    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TURNPIKE E-ZPASS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Jacobs</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Jacobs, Andrew</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Turnpike e-zpass**New Jersey Turnpike Authority says electronic tolls will start September 30 after a two-year delay; announces a 20 percent toll hike for motorists without discount tags (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The New Jersey Turnpike Authority last week announced the arrival of electronic tolls starting Sept. 30, after a two-year of delay and $16 million in overspending. Drivers with the pass will be able to drive from Boston to Philadelphia without having to stop at  toll plazas. But motorists are also getting a toll increase and a system of 8 percent discounts that rewards drivers who use the turnpike during off-peak hours. For those without the windshield-mounted tags, the price increase will be 20 percent.</p>
        <p>Andrew Jacobs</p>
      </block>
